a.com/files/images/story/2025/1749765613_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=3840\" srcset=\"https://www.benzinga.com/files/images/story/2025/1749765613_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=1920 1x, https://www.benzinga.com/files/images/story/2025/1749765613_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=3840 2x\" style=\"border:none;bottom:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:block;height:0;left:0;margin:auto;max-height:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;min-width:100%;padding:0;position:absolute;right:0;top:0;width:0;object-fit:contain\"/></noscript></span></div><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">Finally -- what's the point of all this? The key insight to take from this article is to note how much of a difference compounded returns can make in your cash growth over a period of time.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><em>This article was generated by Benzinga's automated content engine and reviewed by an editor.</em></p><!--/$--></div></div>",
